OL,7,FPembrokeshire faces a projected
OL,8,Ffunding gap of #31.9m. That figure has
OL,9,Fincreased from #27.1m in December, and
OL,10,F#28.4m in January, when it was
OL,11,Fdescribed as "by far the highest
OL,12,Ffunding gap in our history," by
OL,13,FCabinet Member for Corporate Finance
OL,14,FCllr Alec Cormack.
OL,16,FDeputy leader Cllr Paul Miller called
OL,17,Ffor a change to the budget at
OL,18,FWednesday's meeting, proposing a 12.5%
OL,19,Fincrease instead.
